quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  20,99,Thus We relate to you some information of what happened before. And indeed We have given you from Us a Reminder
  20,100,"Whoever turns away from it, verily, they will bear a heavy burden on the Day of Resurrection"
  20,101,They will abide in that -- and evil indeed will it be that load for them on the Day of Resurrection
  20,102,"The Day when the Sur will be blown: that Day, We shall gather the criminals blue-eyed"
  20,103,"They will speak in a very low voice to each other (saying): \"You stayed not longer than ten"
  20,104,"We know very well what they will say, when the best among them in knowledge and wisdom will say: \"You stayed no longer than a day"
  20,105,"And they ask you concerning the mountains. Say: \"My Lord will blast them and scatter them as particles of dust"
  20,106,Then He shall leave it as a level smooth plain
  20,107,You will see therein no crookedness nor curve
  20,108,"On that Day mankind will follow strictly (the voice of) Allah's caller, no crookedness (that is without going to the right or left of that voice) will they show him (Allah's caller). And all voices will be humbled for the Most Gracious (Allah), and nothing shall you hear except Hamsa"
  20,109,"On that day no intercession shall avail, except the one for whom the Most Gracious has given permission and whose word is acceptable to Him"
  20,110,"He knows what happens to them, and what will happen to them, but they will never encompass anything of His knowledge"
  20,111,"And (all) faces shall be humbled before the Ever Living, the Sustainer. And he who carried wrongdoing, will be indeed a complete failure"
  20,112,"And he who works deeds of righteousness, while he is a believer, then he will have no fear of injustice, nor of any curtailment"
  20,113,"And thus We have sent it down as a Qur'an in Arabic, and have explained therein in detail the warnings, in order that they may have Taqwa, or that it may cause them to have a lesson from it"